The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 900) A Christmas special for UK television from 1968 that wasn?t 

released for the next three decades. The Rolling Stones plays host to performances 

by Jethro Tull, the Who, Marianne Faithfull, Dirty Mac (a supergroup featuring 

John Lennon, Eric Clapton and Keith Richards) and play a tune or six themselves. 

THE EVENT

 (Prinsep Ghat, 6.30 pm, December 27 to 30) The classical music soiree, conceived 

by Amit Chaudhuri and presented by Seagull Foundation for the Arts, features vocalists 

Aniruddha Bhattacharya, Arnab Chatterjee and Arshad Ali Khan, and Debashish Bhattacharya 

on guitar. 

THE DISPLAY

 (CIMA 

Design, Forum) The ready-to-wear collection created exclusively for the Forum 

lifestyle store by Nandita Basu includes trousers, kurtas, kurtis and jackets 

in natural fabrics. Dress up in fine Indian craftsmanship with a contemporary 

flair. 




